<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 7:12PM CDT  by NWS Norman-Oklahoma City</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northeastern
Jackson, southwestern Kiowa and southeastern Greer Counties through
745 PM CDT...
At 711 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southwest of Martha, moving northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Altus, Blair, Martha, Friendship, Altus Air Force Base, Warren, Tom
Steed Reservoir and Hester.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
